other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring 10 mm and fluid-filled with mucosal hyper enhancement, adjacent fat stranding and a 0.5 x 0.3 cm appendicolith within the body. No extraluminal air. Minimal bilateral lower lobe atelectasis with no pleural effusion. Normal findings in liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, kidneys, and bladder.
